-2000-0323","Microsoft Jet 数据库引擎 Text I-ISAM 组件文本文件修改漏洞","HIGH",7.6,"1999-07-28T04:00:00.000",0,0],["AVE-2000-0908","CVE-2000-0353","University of Washington Pine 远程代码执行漏洞","CRITICAL",10.0,"1999-06-28T04:00:00.000",0,0],["AVE-2000-0103","CVE-2000-0118","RedHat Linux su 程序登录失败日志缺失导致密码暴力破解漏洞","HIGH",7.2,"1999-06-09T04:00:00.000",0,0],["AVE-2000-0277","CVE-2000-0333","Let me analyze this CVE: - CVE-2000-0333 - Affected products: tcpdump, Ethereal (Wireshark's former name) - Vulnerability type: DNS Decoder Infinite Loop - 拒绝服务漏洞 (Denial of Service) - The issue is in the DNS decoder that enters an infinite loop when processing malformed DNS packets The format should be: \"厂商 产品 漏洞类型\" For this vulnerability, the products are tcpdump and Ethereal. Let me craft a title that captures the vendor, product, and vulnerability type. The vendor would be the tcpdump group / Ethereal project, products are tcpdump and Ethereal, vulnerability type is 拒绝服务漏洞. Title: tcpdump/Ethereal DNS 解析器无限循环拒绝服务漏洞 Actually, let me think about this more carefully. The format is \"厂商 产品 漏洞类型\". - 厂商: Since tcpdump is from the tcpdump group and Ethereal was the predecessor to Wireshark, I could say \"tcpdump Group\" but that's not common. Typically we'd just say the product name as the vendor/product combination. - 产品: tcpdump/Ethereal - 漏洞类型: DNS 解析器无限循环拒绝服务漏洞","MEDIUM",5.0,"1999-05-31T04:00:00.000",0,0],["AVE-2000-0340","CVE-2000-0412","John Donoghue Knapster/gnapster 客户端任意文件读取漏洞","HIGH",7.5,"1999-05-01T04:00:00.000",0,0],["AVE-2000-0137","CVE-2000-0153","Microsoft Personal Web Server 远程目录遍历漏洞","MEDIUM",5.0,"1999-03-26T05:00:00.000",0,0],["AVE-2000-0017","CVE-2000-0019","{\"_meta\":{},\"stopReason\":\"end_turn\",\"usage\":{\"inputTokens\":16251,\"outputTokens\":36,\"totalTokens\":16287}}","LOW",2.1,"1999-03-04T05:00:00.000",0,0],["AVE-2000-0154","CVE-2000-0054","SolutionScripts Home Free 1.0 search.cgi 目录遍历漏洞","MEDIUM",5.0,"1999-01-03T05:00:00.000",0,0]]